						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar in the Mallikārjuna temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla II—A.D. 1139.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Siddhārthi, Kā[rttika], Puṇṇami, Monday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkramaṇa.</hi> The details are irregular. The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1139, November 7, Tuesday.</hi> and the said <hi rend="italic">saṁkramaṇa</hi> did not occur that day.</p>						

						<p>The inscription records a gift of land to god Mallikārjuna at the <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> village <hi rend="bold">[Ka]takanahaḷḷi</hi> by <hi rend="italic">Tārkika-Chūḍāmaṇi</hi> Kēs11ava-paṇḍita and Mādhavapaṇḍita. The gift was entrusted to Āditya-Ghaisāsa.</p>						

						</summary>
